Lead time a göre cancellation yüzdelerinin dağılımı¶

counts_data = data.groupby(['lead_time','is_canceled']).size().reset_index(name='counts')

counts_data = counts_data.pivot_table(index=['lead_time'], columns='is_canceled')

counts_data.columns = counts_data.columns.droplevel().rename(None)

counts_data = counts_data.reset_index()

counts_data = counts_data.fillna(0)

counts_data['Cancellation Rate'] = counts_data.iloc[:,2] / (counts_data.iloc[:,1] + counts_data.iloc[:,2])

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))

sns.regplot(x=counts_data.lead_time, y=counts_data['Cancellation Rate'])

plt.show()

city_data = bookings[bookings.hotel == 'City Hotel']

city = city_data.groupby(['arrival_date_year','arrival_date_month']).size().reset_index(name='counts')

city['realized_accommodation'] = city_data[city_data.is_canceled == 0].groupby(['arrival_date_year','arrival_date_month']).size().reset_index(name='counts')['counts']

city_2016 = city[city.arrival_date_year == 2016]

new_order = ['January', 'February', 'March', 'April', 'May', 'June', 'July', 'August', 'September', 'October', 'November', 'December']

city_2016 = city_2016.set_index('arrival_date_month').reindex(new_order, axis=0).reset_index()

city_2016['cancellations'] = city_2016['counts'] - city_2016['realized_accommodation']

colors = ['#FF9999', '#00BFFF','#C1FFC1','#CAE1FF','#FFDEAD']

r = range(12)

barWidth = 0.5

plt.figure(figsize=(15,6))

ax1 = plt.bar(r, city_2016.realized_accommodation, 
              color=colors[0], edgecolor='white', width=barWidth, label="Realized Accommodation")

ax2 = plt.bar(r, city_2016.cancellations, bottom = np.array(city_2016.realized_accommodation), 
              color=colors[1], edgecolor='white', width=barWidth, label='Cancellations')

plt.title('City Hotel')

plt.legend()

plt.xticks(r, new_order, fontweight='bold')

plt.ylabel("Total Bookings")

for r1, r2 in zip(ax1, ax2):
    
    h1 = r1.get_height()
    
    h2 = r2.get_height()
    
    plt.text(r1.get_x() + r1.get_width() / 2., h1 / 2., "%d" % h1, ha="center", 
             va="center", color="white", fontsize=10, fontweight="bold")
    
    plt.text(r2.get_x() + r2.get_width() / 2., h1 + h2 / 2., "%d" % h2, ha="center", 
             va="center", color="white", fontsize=10, fontweight="bold")

model_data = bookings

model_data = model_data[model_data.country.notna()]

model_data = model_data[model_data.children.notna()]

model_data = model_data.drop(['agent','company','reservation_status','reservation_status_date'], axis=1)

model_data2 = pd.get_dummies(data = model_data, columns = ['hotel','arrival_date_year','arrival_date_month','arrival_date_week_number',
                                             'arrival_date_day_of_month','meal','country','market_segment',
                                             'distribution_channel','reserved_room_type','assigned_room_type',
                                             'deposit_type','customer_type'])

Q1 = model_data2.adr.quantile(0.25)

Q3 = model_data2.adr.quantile(0.75)

IQR = Q3 - Q1

model_data2 = model_data2[(model_data2.adr > (Q1 - 1.5 * IQR)) & (model_data2.adr < (Q3 + 1.5 * IQR))]

Q1 = model_data2.lead_time.quantile(0.25)

Q3 = model_data2.lead_time.quantile(0.75)

IQR = Q3 - Q1

model_data2 = model_data2[(model_data2.lead_time > (Q1 - 1.5 * IQR)) & (model_data2.lead_time < (Q3 + 1.5 * IQR))]

model_data2.lead_time = (model_data2.lead_time - model_data2.lead_time.mean()) / model_data2.lead_time.std()

model_data2.stays_in_weekend_nights = (model_data2.stays_in_weekend_nights - model_data2.stays_in_weekend_nights.mean()) / model_data2.stays_in_weekend_nights.std()

def from_portugal(model_data):
    if (model_data['country'] == 'PRT'):
        val = 1
    else:
        val = 0
    return val

def booking_changes(model_data):
    if (model_data['booking_changes'] == 0):
        val = 1
    else:
        val = 0
    return val

def total_of_special_requests(model_data):
    if (model_data['total_of_special_requests'] == 0):
        val = 1
    else:
        val = 0
    return val

def is_family(model_data):
    if ((model_data['adults'] > 0) & (model_data['children'] > 0)):
        val = 1
    elif ((model_data['adults'] > 0) & (model_data['babies'] > 0)):
        val = 1
    else:
        val = 0
    return val

def model_evaluation(model):
    
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    
    trainset_predictions = model.predict(X_train)
    
    trainset_accuracy = metrics.accuracy_score(trainset_predictions,y_train)
    
    print("Trainset Accuracy : %s" % "{0:.3%}".format(trainset_accuracy))
    
    print("\nTrainset Cross Validation Scores : ",cross_val_score(model, X_train, y_train, cv=5))
    
    print('\nConfusion Matrix:\n {}\n\nAUC Score: {}'.format(confusion_matrix(y_train,trainset_predictions), roc_auc_score(y_train,trainset_predictions)))
    
    testset_predictions = model.predict(X_test)
    
    testset_accuracy = metrics.accuracy_score(testset_predictions,y_test)
    
    print("\nTestset Accuracy : %s" % "{0:.3%}".format(testset_accuracy))
         
    print("\nTestset Cross Validation Scores : ",cross_val_score(model, X_test, y_test, cv=5)) 
    
    print('\nConfusion Matrix:\n {}\n\nAUC Score: {}'.format(confusion_matrix(y_test,testset_predictions), roc_auc_score(y_test,testset_predictions)))
    
    y_prob = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1]
    
    false_positive_rate, true_positive_rate, threshold = roc_curve(y_test, y_prob)
    
    roc_auc = auc(false_positive_rate, true_positive_rate)
    
    plt.figure(figsize = (10,10))
    
    plt.title('Receiver Operating Characteristic')
    
    plt.plot(false_positive_rate, true_positive_rate, color = 'red', label = 'AUC = %0.2f' % roc_auc)
    
    plt.legend(loc = 'lower right')
    
    plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], linestyle = '--')
    
    plt.axis('tight')
    
    plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
    
    plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')

cordat['assigned_room_type'] = le.fit_transform(cordat['assigned_room_type'])


cordat['deposit_type'] = le.fit_transform(cordat['deposit_type'])

cordat['customer_type'] = le.fit_transform(cordat['customer_type'])

def get_redundant_pairs(cordat):
    
    pairs_to_drop = set()
    
    cols = cordat.columns
    
    for i in range(0, cordat.shape[1]):
        
        for j in range(0, i+1):
            
            pairs_to_drop.add((cols[i], cols[j]))
    
    return pairs_to_drop

def get_top_abs_correlations(cordat, n=5):
    
    au_corr = cordat.corr().abs().unstack()
    
    labels_to_drop = get_redundant_pairs(cordat)
    
    au_corr = au_corr.drop(labels=labels_to_drop).sort_values(ascending=False)
    
    return au_corr[0:n]

print("Top Absolute Correlations")

print(get_top_abs_correlations(cordat, 10))

def from_portugal(model_data):
    if (model_data['country'] == 'PRT'):
        val = 1
    else:
        val = 0
    return val

def booking_changes(model_data):
    if (model_data['booking_changes'] == 0):
        val = 1
    else:
        val = 0
    return val

def total_of_special_requests(model_data):
    if (model_data['total_of_special_requests'] == 0):
        val = 1
    else:
        val = 0
    return val

def is_family(model_data):
    if ((model_data['adults'] > 0) & (model_data['children'] > 0)):
        val = 1
    elif ((model_data['adults'] > 0) & (model_data['babies'] > 0)):
        val = 1
    else:
        val = 0
    return val

model_data = model_data[model_data.country.notna()]

model_data = model_data[model_data.children.notna()]

model_data["from_portugal"] = model_data.apply(from_portugal, axis = 1)        

model_data["booking_changes"] = model_data.apply(booking_changes, axis = 1)   

model_data["total_of_special_requests"] = model_data.apply(total_of_special_requests, axis = 1)   

model_data["is_family"] = model_data.apply(is_family, axis = 1)   

model_data = model_data.drop(['agent','company','reservation_status','reservation_status_date','country','adults','children','babies'], axis=1)

model_data2 = pd.get_dummies(data = model_data, columns = ['hotel','arrival_date_year','arrival_date_month','arrival_date_week_number',
                                             'arrival_date_day_of_month','meal','market_segment',
                                             'distribution_channel','reserved_room_type','assigned_room_type',
                                             'deposit_type','customer_type'])

Q1 = model_data2.adr.quantile(0.25)

Q3 = model_data2.adr.quantile(0.75)

IQR = Q3 - Q1

model_data2 = model_data2[(model_data2.adr > (Q1 - 1.5 * IQR)) & (model_data2.adr < (Q3 + 1.5 * IQR))]

Q1 = model_data2.lead_time.quantile(0.25)

Q3 = model_data2.lead_time.quantile(0.75)

IQR = Q3 - Q1

model_data2 = model_data2[(model_data2.lead_time > (Q1 - 1.5 * IQR)) & (model_data2.lead_time < (Q3 + 1.5 * IQR))]

model_data2.lead_time = (model_data2.lead_time - model_data2.lead_time.mean()) / model_data2.lead_time.std()

model_data2.stays_in_weekend_nights = (model_data2.stays_in_weekend_nights - model_data2.stays_in_weekend_nights.mean()) / model_data2.stays_in_weekend_nights.std()

model_data2.stays_in_week_nights = (model_data2.stays_in_week_nights - model_data2.stays_in_week_nights.mean()) / model_data2.stays_in_week_nights.std()


model_data2.previous_cancellations = (model_data2.previous_cancellations - model_data2.previous_cancellations.mean()) / model_data2.previous_cancellations.std()

model_data2.previous_bookings_not_canceled = (model_data2.previous_bookings_not_canceled - model_data2.previous_bookings_not_canceled.mean()) / model_data2.previous_bookings_not_canceled.std()

model_data2.days_in_waiting_list = (model_data2.days_in_waiting_list - model_data2.days_in_waiting_list.mean()) / model_data2.days_in_waiting_list.std()

model_data2.adr = (model_data2.adr - model_data2.adr.mean()) / model_data2.adr.std()

model_data2.required_car_parking_spaces = (model_data2.required_car_parking_spaces - model_data2.required_car_parking_spaces.mean()) / model_data2.required_car_parking_spaces.std()

y = model_data2["is_canceled"]

def model_evaluation(model):
    
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    
    trainset_predictions = model.predict(X_train)
    
    trainset_accuracy = metrics.accuracy_score(trainset_predictions,y_train)
    
    print("Trainset Accuracy : %s" % "{0:.3%}".format(trainset_accuracy))
    
    print("\nTrainset Cross Validation Scores : ",cross_val_score(model, X_train, y_train, cv=5))
    
    print('\nConfusion Matrix:\n {}\n\nAUC Score: {}'.format(confusion_matrix(y_train,trainset_predictions), roc_auc_score(y_train,trainset_predictions)))
    
    testset_predictions = model.predict(X_test)
    
    testset_accuracy = metrics.accuracy_score(testset_predictions,y_test)
    
    print("\nTestset Accuracy : %s" % "{0:.3%}".format(testset_accuracy))
         
    print("\nTestset Cross Validation Scores : ",cross_val_score(model, X_test, y_test, cv=5)) 
    
    print('\nConfusion Matrix:\n {}\n\nAUC Score: {}'.format(confusion_matrix(y_test,testset_predictions), roc_auc_score(y_test,testset_predictions)))
    
    y_prob = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1]
    
    false_positive_rate, true_positive_rate, threshold = roc_curve(y_test, y_prob)
    
    roc_auc = auc(false_positive_rate, true_positive_rate)
    
    plt.figure(figsize = (10,10))
    
    plt.title('Receiver Operating Characteristic')
    
    plt.plot(false_positive_rate, true_positive_rate, color = 'red', label = 'AUC = %0.2f' % roc_auc)
    
    plt.legend(loc = 'lower right')
    
    plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], linestyle = '--')
    
    plt.axis('tight')
    
    plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
    
    plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
